 HOST:<br>Kiryukan Dojo<br><br>THIS MONTH'S VENUE:<br>International School Manila gym<br>Fort Bonifacio <br>Taguig City<br><br>All
are invited to the 92nd FFA monthly interclub practice. This series of
joint monthly practice sessions started in September 2000. The FFA is
home to some of the oldest, most experienced Aikido dojos in the
Philippines. The FFA is recognized by Japan Aikikai.<br><br>PRACTITIONERS FROM NON-AFFILIATED DOJOS VERY WELCOME.</small></span><small><span style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;"></span></small><br><br><small><br style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;"><span style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;">

Getting there:</span><br style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;"><br style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;"><span style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;">International School Manila is on 38th
Parkway in Fort Boni, Taguig City. The campus is near Market! Market!
and the Serendra development. To get there:</span><br style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;"><br style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;"><span style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;">A. DRIVING YOUR CAR</span><br style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;"><span style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;">Option
1: From C-5, coming from QC/Pasig (i.e., you're driving south). Cross
the C-5/Kalayaan intersection, then take the first exit ramp that you
encounter on your right. Upon completing this uphill exit ramp, you'll
come to a traffic light; turn right at the light. You're now on 38th
Parkway. Along this road, ISM gate is to your right. ISM security will
take your name and license, and you will be allowed
to park underneath the school building. </span><br style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;"><br style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;"><span style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;">Option 2: From Makati
Central Business District (i.e., you're going east). From Gil Puyat
(formerly Buendia) driving eastwards, take the Kalayaan flyover into
Fort Boni. Kalayaan flyover gives out directly onto 32nd Street. Follow
32nd Street all the way almost to the end, until you hit a traffic
light at which you can see Market! Market!/Serendra on your right. Turn
left at that traffic light; you're now on 38th Parkway. Proceed as
above.</span><br style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;"><br style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;"><span style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;">B) USING PUBLIC TRANSPORTATION</span><br style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;"><span style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;">Take the Market! Market! jeep from Guadalupe; make your way on foot from Market! Market! to ISM.</span></small><br><br><small><span style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;"></span></small><h3 style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><font face="Arial" size="2"><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial; font-weight: 400;"><i><span style="font-style: italic;">&nbsp;</span></i></span></font></h3>



      
      
      
      



      
      
      
